# Broadcasting Configuration Examples

## Option 1: Local Development with Laravel Reverb

```env
BROADCAST_DRIVER=reverb
REVERB_APP_ID=12345
REVERB_APP_KEY=your-reverb-key
REVERB_APP_SECRET=your-reverb-secret
REVERB_HOST=localhost
REVERB_PORT=8080
REVERB_SCHEME=http

# Optional: For WebSocket proxy
VITE_REVERB_HOST=localhost
VITE_REVERB_PORT=8080
VITE_REVERB_SCHEME=ws
```

## Option 2: Production with Pusher

```env
BROADCAST_DRIVER=pusher
PUSHER_APP_ID=123456
PUSHER_APP_KEY=your-pusher-key
PUSHER_APP_SECRET=your-pusher-secret
PUSHER_APP_CLUSTER=mt1

# Frontend configuration (these are public)
VITE_PUSHER_APP_KEY=your-pusher-key
VITE_PUSHER_APP_CLUSTER=mt1
VITE_BROADCAST_DRIVER=pusher
```

## Option 3: Development without Broadcasting (Fallback)

```env
BROADCAST_DRIVER=null
```

## Pusher Setup

1. Sign up at https://pusher.com
2. Create a new app
3. Go to "App Keys"
4. Copy and paste the credentials above
5. Your cluster will be shown (e.g., "mt1", "us2", "ap1")

## Laravel Reverb Setup

1. Install: `composer require laravel/reverb`
2. Publish config: `php artisan vendor:publish --provider="Laravel\Reverb\ReverberServiceProvider"`
3. Generate keys: `php artisan reverb:install`
4. Start server: `php artisan reverb:start`

The Reverb installation will auto-generate app keys and store them in `.env`.

## Testing Broadcasting

```bash
# Test with artisan tinker
php artisan tinker

# Dispatch a test event
event(new App\Events\StudentCreated(\App\Models\Student::first()));
```

## Debugging

Enable debug mode for WebSocket connections:

```env
BROADCAST_DRIVER=reverb
LOG_CHANNEL=stack
LOG_LEVEL=debug
```

Watch logs:
```bash
tail -f storage/logs/laravel.log
```
